(04:01) and and then at the bottom you've got $30,000 cars which is accessible to to just about everybody right in the US at least. And so for me, if I'm working with a business, especially if you're starting out right now, you're under three million, looking at this and thinking, okay, I'm okay serving fewer people at higher prices so that I can get my chops, learn the skills, price anchor myself in a way so that when you do say, hey, I'm opening up this thing that's a little bit easier for me to fulfill.
(04:25) You'll have the credibility, the perceived likelihood of achievement from your prospects. So they're like, well, this person was charging this much, so now this is a deal, right? And it all exists within the context that we create. This is the frame of mind. This is the frame of reference. And so I prefer to build business bu build businesses from the top down rather than the bottom up.
