(06:34) Now in general most times when you do things that are easier for you it's less value to the prospect. Not always, but in general. And that that's why it takes a lot of time and thinking to create things that are very high value and easy to fulfill, right? And so my rule of thumb when someone is starting out is create flow first, get the yeses first, even if it's hard to fulfill, make money, and then when you look at all the things you did, I'll bet you there are some things in that process that you said you were going to fulfill on that the person didn't
(06:57) actually get a lot of value from, and they may have been really hard for you to fulfill. So you can start cutting those pieces out, adding things that you didn't have, and then you you're basically iterating on your offer until you finally have the stack of things that are very valuable that you can provide to them.
